{
  "negotiation_summary": "I am Austria, vulnerable in the Balkans with only BUD, VIE, TRI. No firm alliances exist yet. I communicated urgency: Russia and Turkey both threaten Balkan pressure; Germany and Italy are potential partners but noncommittal. I sought commitments for stable borders and reciprocal support vs. Russia/Turkey. Key tacit outcomes: no binding promises received; Germany and Italy remain noncommittal but open to talks; Russia currently holds 4 centers and is the primary strategic threat to my south/east if it turns south; Turkey controls the southern flank and could either attack me or cooperate vs. Russia. England and France are irrelevant to immediate Balkan security. I must secure clear written commitments before moving forces out of defensive posture. Important pledge to myself: do not trust verbal assurances; require concrete move support or demilitarized zones before risking units.",
  "intent": "S1901M: Maintain defensive posture in the Balkans. Planned moves I intend to make: A VIE hold, A BUD support A VIE (or hold if a better support target is required), F TRI hold (or move to ION only if I secure a written non-aggression/coordination with Italy/Turkey). I will not provoke Russia or Turkey this turn. I will seek explicit written agreements from Italy (regarding Venice/Naples) and Turkey (regarding Smyrna/Ankara/Consolidation) and a clear message from Germany that it will not support Russian expansion into Galicia. I intend to fulfil these intentions; if I receive explicit support offers (e.g., Turkish promise to not move to BUL/SMY aggression and to support A CON vs. RUS if needed), I may adjust F TRI to IONC or ADR depending on confirmations. I will refuse any orders that abandon BUD or VIE

{
  "negotiation_summary": "I prepared a cautious, defensive posture: emphasize secure borders, control of the Straits, and incremental gains. I warned neighbors that Black Sea and Balkan instability (notably Russia's fleet at SEV and StP/SC and Austria's presence in Trieste/Vie) make guarantees of my southern and northern flanks essential. I sought DMZ-like assurances for the Aegean and Sea of Marmara to prevent surprise fleets into the Straits, and requested non-aggression or neutral stances from England, Italy, and Austria in exchange for Turkey avoiding early aggression in the Balkans. I indicated willingness to coordinate with Germany against Russian naval pressure in the Black Sea and to accept limited Austro-Turkish cooperation in the Balkans if Austria refrains from pushing south of Serbia. I offered Italy and England guarantees against Turkish moves into Greek islands provided they do not support Greek or Russian operations that threaten the Straits. No binding multi-power coalition was agreed; assurances are tentative and conditional on observing moves. Key point to remember: demand explicit DMZs or non-support promises around the Straits and Aegean before trusting neighbors.",
  "intent": "Hold defensive lines and secure the Straits. Planned orders (intended to submit unless contradicted by new, reliable deals): F ANK hold (protects Black Sea access and Straits), A CON hold (covers Constantinople and supports defense of Straits), A SMY to ARM (advance to Armenia is cautious but places pressure on Russian southern flank and creates room for negotiation); if offered explicit DMZ/non-support guarantees for the Aegean/Straits, adjust: A SMY hold instead and consider F ANK to BLA only with German coordination. I intend to fulfill these moves unless concrete, verifiable promises arrive that make an alternative safer (e.g., binding DMZ guarantees allowing

{
  "negotiation_summary": "I have positioned as an expansive, patient power seeking flexible partnerships across north and south. No binding agreements recorded this phase, but priorities communicated: seek demilitarized Baltic approaches with England/Scandinavia (avoid immediate conflict over Sweden/Norway/Finland) in exchange for cooperation against Germany by supporting pressure on Kie/Prussia lines; offer Turkey coordination in the south to avoid early clash over Ankara/Black Sea and to partition Balkans peacefully (Austria to be engaged to limit Austro-Turkish friction). Emphasized forecasting northern opening (possible English support against Germany/Kie) and southern opening (Turkish or Austro pressure through Constantinople/Serbia/Rumania), proposing mutual guarantees: Russia will not immediately attack Sweden/Norway if England does not support Germany against me; Russia will limit advances into Rum/Serbia if Turkey/Austria avoid moves into Sevastopol/Ukraine and respect Rumanian neutrality. No explicit written moves exchanged, only diplomatic framework and offers of cooperation.",
  "intent": "S1901M intents: Defend and consolidate while keeping options open. Planned orders I intend to issue: F STP/SC hold (maintain Scandinavian/ice access); F SEV hold (secure southern flank); A MOS -> WAR or hold depending on northern tensions (default: A MOS supports A WAR if needed, otherwise MOS -> WAR to threaten Galicia); A WAR hold or move to GAL if Austria's posture appears weak. I will honor proposed non-aggression with England and Turkey as long as they reciprocate; if England moves aggressively into Scandinavia or supports Germany vs me, I will shift A MOS -> PRU or STP moves accordingly. Intend to fulfill promises to avoid immediate aggression into Turkish/Austrian zones unless proactively attacked or betrayed.",
